<div class="bibEntry"><p class="bib special">466. Favre, Jean Paul. Color and und et Communication. Zurich: ABC Edition, 1979. 167 pp. Index, color illus. ISBN 3-85504-056-7. </p><p class="annot">Color is thoroughly discussed as it relates to signage, product identification and packaging, advertising and marketing, and creation and reinforcement of corporate image. A major portion of the book consists of captioned color illustrations taken primarily from product packages and advertisements. Written in a clear, concise manner, the text is provided in English, German, and French. This excellent and enduring book on Swiss design is filled with interesting and useful information on color preferences, association, and symbolism and their impact in marketing. </p></div>
